{
  "stem": "1799.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he had a lot of faith in the future of-- he didn't see the threat of Hitler as much as he-- well, maybe he wasn't being realistic.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It didn't appear to him as such a big threat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had so much confidence in the country, as such.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At one time, my mother came up with a adopting process, or a foster family, that she located in New York, and pointed out to my father that she could send me to that family, and then maybe, I could continue to go to school there.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then when my father found out that they were not kosher, he just nixed the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I was pretty close, there, in the mid '30s to being sent to the United States, if it hadn't been for that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Besides, he didn't want me to leave the family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were a closely knit family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother played bridge at least once a week.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was active with the other Jewish ladies in the city.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think, among her friends, she also had some non-Jewish ladies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had family in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she would very often travel to Berlin, which was just like an hour's train ride away and spend time with her family, there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That family was not kosher, and my father hardly ever visited there, although I had.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were well-to-do people.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had a summer home near a lake not far from Berlin.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they had boats, and they had some great recreational activities.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had a very pleasant life, certainly, a bourgeois standard, or a middle class, if not upper middle class, standard.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
